A court ruling against the EFF has important implications for balancing the right to freedom of expression against the right to dignity on social media. Courtesy of #DSTV403 JOHANNESBURG - A court ruling against the EFF has important implications for balancing the right to freedom of expression against the right to dignity on social media, according to the Press Ombudsman Pippa Green. The High Court has ordered the EFF to apologise for and retract defamatory remarks about former finance minister Trevor Manuel. READ: EFF to appeal Manuel court judgment The ruling touched on freedom of expression on social media. Green said the ruling balanced the freedom of expression with the responsibility for what you say. "It's quite a serious judgment and I think probably a landmark judgment about how to use Twitter," Green opined.